  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager (Marine Spare Parts)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Build and expand a customer portfolio for spare parts and equipment servicing sales within the Industrial, Marine, Offshore, and Oil & Gas sectors.</li><li>Maintain high standards of customer service while developing strong client relationships.</li><li>Drive revenue growth by achieving established sales targets and maintaining optimal profit margins.</li><li>Develop and execute sales and marketing initiatives to seize opportunities in domestic and international markets.</li><li>Conduct sales presentations and provide necessary support to clients.</li><li>Research and analyze market trends, competitor activities, and technological advancements.</li><li>Submit regular performance reports, including weekly, monthly, and quarterly updates.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) requirements for all stakeholders.</li><li>Perform additional duties as assigned by management.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma qualification, preferably in Business or Engineering.</li><li>Prior sales experience in Marine, Commercial and Owner Accounts is desirable.</li><li>Familiarity with marine spare parts sales is a plus.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications.</li><li>Strong team player with a positive attitude, integrity, and excellent interpersonal, organizational, and time management skills.</li><li>Capable of managing tasks professionally, independently, and effectively under tight deadlines.</li></ul>",
